white: A four-second scene in Annie Hall that is inexplicably iconic. .
Whatever the fuck Jeff Goldblum is doing with his hands right now.
Literally never turning down a role, because you just love working. .
Reading people’s palms as an excuse to touch their hands.
Throwing your glasses at Conan O’Brien.
What could have been with the animated Jurassic Park series. .
The Aquatic Life of Steve Zissou.
Jeff Goldblum looking at you like you’re the most beautiful person in the world.
Uploading pictures of your crotch to Instagram, ostensibly because of your new belt buckle.
Enjoying being called both Zaddy and Daddy.
Being billed as “Jeff Goldberg” because the movie was just that good.
Lightly chiding interviewers for shying away from homosexuality.
Baboons inexplicably respecting Jeff Goldblum, and nobody else on set.
Asking the women you used to take home if they believe in faeries at the bottom of your yard.
Being a reason for Conan to believe in extraterrestial life.
Wearing twelve rings on one hand.
Four watchable minutes out of an unwatchable movie.
Tom Hiddleston, a very tender lover, I’m sure.
A hapless director making the mistake of thinking a piano can be on set without Jeff Goldblum putting his hands all over it.
Pontificating on how death comes for us all.
Being the only person on set who can control the baboons.
Searching your own hashtag on Instagram.
Convincing Steven Spielberg to keep your character in the movie, and being the most popular one.
Manspreading no matter how tight your skinny jeans are.
Absolutely unnecessary focus on people’s feet.
When the entire internet encourages your shameless narcissism.
Playing somebody’s gay dad on Glee. .
Saying, “I’m like Sherlock Holmes,” and never justifying it.
Never having been convinced that anybody knows anything. .
Interrupting normal conversations to sing snatches of jazz.
Repeatedly calling Wes Anderson a genius.
An appearance on Friends that, for some reason, includes piss. .
When directors cast Jeff Goldblum as a WASP and just play it straight.
Jeff Goldblum artfully avoiding questions about whether he’s gay or straight.
Taika Waititi setting your brain on fire. .
Wearing sunglasses all the time, but only to appear cool, and not to appear “druggy”.
Jeff Goldblum realizing he can’t say whatever he was about to say on television.
The Adventures of Buckaroo Banzai Across The Eighth Dimension.
Going to town on a salt lick.
Doing that thing where you transfer wine from your mouth to her mouth.
Re-enacting entire scenes from your filmography.
Playing Republican George Gorton despite being hot, vibrant, and visibly Jewish.
Asking Emilie if you can take some girls home with, “Come on, they’re hot!”.
Licking a martini glass LIKE THAT.
